The question was about a tax relief for employment. The answer can be found in the following source:

[1] source=ZAKO4687_zddpo-2_NPB23.html, chunk_id=chunk_000584, article=55.b. člen

The tax relief for employment is described in article 55.b of the ZDDPO-2 statute. It states that an employer can reduce the tax base by 45% of the salary of a person who is younger than 29 years old, older than 55 years old, or in a profession where there is a lack of job seekers, if the person was not employed by the employer or their associated person in the last 24 months. This tax relief can be applied for the first 24 months of employment and for the following years up to 24 months. For persons in a profession where there is a lack of job seekers, the relief can be applied if the shortage is defined on a list established by a minister in charge of work, in agreement with the minister in charge of finance, at least every two years. The employer can apply this relief only if they increase the total number of employees in the tax period in which they hire a new employee for whom they apply the relief, and the increase in the number of employees is calculated by comparing the number of employees on the last day of the tax period with the average number of employees in the previous 12 months or fewer months if the period was shorter. The relief can also be applied for a person younger than 25 years old who is employed for the first time, but the relief cannot exceed the tax base.

