(1) The tax authority shall identify the following persons with a separate VAT identification number:
(2) The VAT identification number is the tax number with the prefix SI.
(3) The tax authority shall publish on its website, in accordance with the law governing the tax procedure, the following data on taxpayers for the purposes of verifying VAT identification:
Note:
The amended third paragraph of Article 79 shall apply from 1 January 2026.
a) the name, address and tax number;
b) the name or title, registered office and address and tax number of a person who is not a natural person;
c) the VAT identification number, the date of registration or deregistration for VAT purposes;
d) a list of VAT groups with the names or titles, addresses and tax numbers of the members, and the dates of entry into and exit from the VAT group of individual members.

